result.execSummary:
The defendant Jonathon Edward Oaks was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of Methamphetamine [Modifiers: Second or Subsequent Offense, Penalties for Felonies-Class "I" Felony], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(g).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Apprs: CO: SRN, Rpr: Kasten, Clerk: Scobey. ADA:   Amber L Hahn   DF ATTY:  Daniel J. Chapman   DF:  Jonathon Edward Oaks appeared from jail. Case called at 11:21 a.m. Set for pre-trial. Plea questionnaire waiver filed. DE has been accepted to Pierce County Drug Court. Atty Chapman informs Court of agreement to plea to Count 1 and Count 2 to be read in and dismissed.  DE pleads guilty to Count 1 with repeater. DE sworn. Court informs DE of rights. Attorneys stipulate to the facts, Court finds DE freely, voluntarily, and knowingly makes plea. Court accepts plea, finds factual basis, and finds DE guilty of Count 1 with repeater. On motion of the State, Count 2 read in and dismissed. PSI waived by attorneys. DE waives PSI. Court waives PSI. Sentencing recommendations. DE makes statement.  Court orders:  S/W, 3 years probation, with conditions, concurrent with Pierce County probation.
Conditions of probation are:

-9 months jail, concurrent to Pierce County jail time. 6 months STAYED to be used by Agent.
-Huber granted for work and treatment.
-Regular and random testing.
-AODA and follow any recommended treatment.
-Absolute sobriety:  Zero alcohol, zero controlled substances, zero prescribed medications (except as taken and prescribed for you by a physician) in your system, on your person, or in your possession at all times while this case is ongoing. This prohibition includes drug paraphernalia.
-Not to associate with any persons known or suspected to be involved in use, trafficking, dealing or manufacturing of illegal drugs except in a treatment setting.
-DE to successfully complete Pierce County Drug Court.
-Court costs and supervision costs payable through probation.

Court notes 45 days credit against any ultimate sentence. Adjourned at 11:59 a.m.
to Transport. Signed by SRN on 8/26/2014. c: DA, cc: Missy, Fax: Sheriff and Jail. km

It is hereby ordered, as a condition of the defendant's bond/bail in the above-captioned case, that he/she have absolutely NO CONTACT whatsoever with the complaining witness, or with any of the following named persons and/or locations, Daisy F.  The term "no contact" is hereby defined as no contact in person, by telephone, by way of electronic device, email, facsimile, through the mail, and/or through a third person.  The aforementioned condition of bond/bail is set pursuant to Sec. 969.02(3)(d), Wis Stats.

Further, it is ORDERED that if the defendant fails to comply with the conditions of his/her bond/bail that he/she may be charged with the offense of bailjumping contrary to Sec. 946.49(1)(a), Wis. Stats.
